  current_length = 2\n                j = i + 2\n                while j < n and nums[j] == nums[j - 2]:\n                    current_length += 1\n                    j += 1\n                max_length = max(max_length, current_length)\n        \n        return max_length if max_length > 1 else -1\n```\n\nThis solution iterates through the list `nums` and checks for the start of an alternating subarray. If it finds a potential start (where `nums[i + 1] == nums[i] + 1`), it continues to check the subsequent elements to see if they form an alternating pattern. It keeps track of the current length of the alternating subarray and updates the maximum length found. If no alternating subarray of length greater than 1 is found, it returns -1.", "estimated_date": 1688256000000}